## Reasoning is load-bearing

Your `reasoning` field is read by future-round agents and by a human reviewer. Be specific: name
the instruction, the accounts, the seeds, the CPI target, the attack pattern. "I considered the
missing owner check on `vault` but ruled it out because the Anchor `Account<Vault>` type already
enforces owner = this program" is the right granularity; "I thought about it and decided Y" is not.

